WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Tanglink' is a variation on the average run-of-the-mill
sliding-tiles-puzzle... with a little twist: in this game, tiles
have geometric shapes and are linked together. The idea is to move
those tiles at their proper places, so they replicate various
patterns...

  Other tiles have no shapes and are there, as the saying goes:
"just for the ride" and have no purpose, except to complicate the
game a little... of course, there is the required empty space, so
you can move the tiles on the board...

  Complete each game board in the least amount of moves possible.

  Have fun!

FEATURES
--------

-Simple installation: just run the game and play!

-100 game patterns to match.

-The game can be played by using the mouse or the cursor keys on
 the keyboard.

-Small package, the Lha archive is smaller than 50K, so it doesn't
 take ages to download :)

-The game plays on the Workbench screen and its window is
 resizeable.

